{
  "texts": [
    "Further work should incorporate the diverse applications of ML into chemical reaction optimization campaigns to open new avenues for research and discovery.",
    "In particular, ML tools have great potential for the planning of reaction optimization campaigns to assist the selection of categorical chemical variables (e.g., catalysts, ligands, additives, etc.).",
    "Christensen et al. [15] have already demonstrated the advantages of applying ML clustering methods to discover new ligands for catalysts that would have been missed if the selection of test ligands had only relied on human chemical intuition.",
    "Taylor et al. [92] also highlighted the use of DFT or ML alternatives to find similarities between reaction models in order to apply efficient multitask learning to chemical reaction optimization.",
    "Another potential application of ML tools is the use of CASP to discover alternative reaction routes, with the potential to improve the efficiency of current manufacturing methods."
  ]
}